      "message": "nits:\n1. Probably should ensure this is UTC.\n2. Probably need to firestore.FixTimestamp this.\n3. Just for sanity, we might want to ensure j.Requested is before j.Created. I can think of two reasons for this:\n A. It would be nice to be able to filter out manually-triggered and periodic jobs later. One way to do so would be to filter out anything where j.Requested \u003d\u003d j.Created. (We could do this other ways, but I think that\u0027s the cleanest/easiest.)\n B. Just in case clocks are slightly out-of-sync and/or timestamps are rounded to a coarser precision, it would be nice to not have to deal with negative numbers for j.Created.Sub(j.Requested).\n\nSame nits for tryjobs.",
